      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the onion is softening, chop your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> chopped creamed coconut </strong>in 150ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and add your <strong>soy sauce</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>garam masala</strong> and <strong>ground cumin</strong> and cook for a further 1 min</p><p>Add your<strong> curry paste</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
